Write a function checkingForFinite that takes two numbers a and b as arguments dividing a by b and checking the result of the division (quotient) by finitude. 
The function must return true if the result is a finite number and false otherwise.

Examples:

checkingForFinite (4, 2) should return true;
checkingForFinite (3, 0) should return false;
checkingForFinite (-1, 0) should return false.

Solution:

function checkingForFinite(a, b){
  return isFinite(a/b);
}
